    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's interesting that you say it's \"undeniable\" that it reduces the necessity to work. wouldn't it be more accurate to say that other things like automation or even a shift in how people value work are more likely the actual drivers, rather than just blaming the safety net? it seems like a bit of a leap to say the spending is the direct cause.",
