      "content": "It is a far more accurate and responsible analysis to point to the influence of structural economic changes like automation, which are undeniable forces reshaping the labor market. Blaming the safety net as the sole driver ignores the massive technological shifts that are fundamentally altering job availability and required skills. The welfare expansion is a secondary factor, at best, while technological displacement is the primary, undeniable cause of workforce changes.",
